==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Putresce
<hw>Pu*tresce"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Putrescent</er>.]</ety> <def>To become putrescent or putrid; to
putrefy.</def></p>

<p><q>Ordinarily sewage does not <qex>putresce</qex> until from
twenty-four to sixty hours after its discharge.</q>
<rj><qau>Nature.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Putrescence</ent>⟦br⟧
